cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on machine learning techniques for perception in autonomous driving, specifically deep neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of these models to adversarial attacks, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of physically realizable attacks and the investigation of their effectiveness in specific scenarios suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the discussion of hijacking attacks and the use of network deconvolution to understand successful attacks suggests a focus on computer security (cs.CR) sub-category.
